Class TreeFitnessAbstract

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.processmining.plugins.etm.fitness.TreeFitnessAbstract
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FitnessEvaluator<NAryTree>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConfigurationFitness, EditDistanceWrapperRTEDAbsolute, FitnessReplay, Generalization, GeneralizationByFitnessReplayDeviation, MultiThreadedFitnessEvaluator, NewMetric, OverallFitness, ParetoFitnessEvaluator, PrecisionEscEdges, PrecisionEscEdgesImproved, PrecisionFlowerSize, PrecisionOperatorCosts, SimplicityDuplMissingAct, SimplicityMixed, SimplicityOperatorAlternation, SimplicityTreeSize, SimplicityUselessNodes

    public abstract class TreeFitnessAbstract
extends java.lang.Object
implements FitnessEvaluator<NAryTree>
    All fitness metrics should extend this abstract Tree Fitness class. They also should either (i) define no constructors or (ii) if they define a constructor also define the public empty constructor that should not fail. If they do this than any fitness metric, even outside this package and currently unknown, will be able to be used by the ETM if ProM has loaded it correctly!
    Author:
    jbuijs

      • deepClone

        public static TreeFitnessAbstract deepClone(TreeFitnessAbstract original,
                            java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Class<TreeFitnessAbstract>,TreeFitnessAbstract> clonedMap)
        This method deeply clones the provided TreeFitnessAbstract. It will automatically call the copy constructor for the TreeFitnessAbstract implementing class with the original instance as a parameter. Iff the original TreeFitnessAbstract indicated that it depends on other TreeFitnessAbstract instances then a copy-constructor is searched and called that takes as input parameters of the original instance and the dependent TreeFitnessAbstract instances, in the order specified in the TreeFitnessInfo object. The correct cloned instance is taken from the clonedMap to be provided to this constructor (e.g. the deep clone is linking to an already cloned instance of that TreeFitnessAbstract class). NOTE: this map should be maintained OUTSIDE this call. For an example implementation see the OverallFitness copy constructor.

        original -
        clonedMap -
